          "items": {
            "preprocessing": "6/7 - Implements configurable downsampling suitable for 30k×30k (target_max_dim), Gaussian blur, and background subtraction with both morphological and large-Gaussian options. Pipeline is coherent, but has minor issues: returns bg_removed twice (preprocessed and bg_removed are identical), and background subtraction parameters may be heavy without tiling/streaming; no explicit dtype/range normalization beyond cv2.subtract.",
            "coarse_detection": "4/7 - Has thresholding (Otsu/adaptive/manual), morphological cleanup, largest external contour selection, and circle fitting (LSQ or minEnclosingCircle). However, coarse_detect is incomplete (does not set radius/success/return properly in shown code), and there is no explicit mapping back to original-scale coordinates using the preprocessing scale factor (critical requirement).",
            "fine_detection": "3/7 - Implements radial sampling along multiple angles with bilinear interpolation and uses 1D diff as gradient. But dual-edge detection function is truncated/incomplete (secondary edge not used, no final selection logic, no sub-pixel refinement), and no robust handling of intensity polarity beyond a comment. Overall only basic framework present.",
            "statistical_analysis": "5/7 - MAD computation and MAD-scaled 3-sigma outlier rejection are correctly implemented and logged; feature point classification into chord-midpoints/high-intensity/outliers exists. However, robust_circle_fit (the step that should produce final robust radius/center) is truncated/incomplete, so robust statistics are not clearly integrated into final radius estimation.",
            "mask_generation": "5/7 - Provides circular and ring mask creation with optional smooth edge, and chord-adaptive cropping that computes per-row/column chord bounds plus bbox crop. However chord detection itself (finding chords from image/gradient) is not implemented, apply_chord_crop_to_image is truncated, and feature point detection relies on statistical_analysis outputs rather than mask-based chord finding."
